<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98655905714432></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98655905714432><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98655905714432>RE: Cleric melee, more on the subject</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98655905714432#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>112 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 6th 8:10 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.96]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmm, well I checked and it wasn't me who said he'd never group with you.&nbsp;&nbsp;(I was worried there for a minute too :))<br><br>My question (politely), What is your defense and AC right now?  Without having your Defense skills maxed your AC is possible 200 or more less than it should be.  When a Shardworm Brood Mother turns on you (and she was just hitting me for almost 200 a shot) and your AC/Defense is low how are you going to survive till the tank can taunt her off.  If there is a trick to this then I'm very interested.  The only time I ever die with a cleric present is when the cleric agro's something and gets killed before I can taunt it off.  Higher AC, maxed defense/dodge all are important for that event (and it will happen) when the MoB turns on you.<br><br>I also question the logic of always using C Heal for tanks.  Again the 45 Cleric who keeps me alive almost never casts C Heal, Selestial Heal is his main heal.  I know not everyone has this spell, but once you get it, this is a much lower agro spell and seems to be more mana efficient.  Oh yeh, and being as I am an SK, I do "chain pull" MoB's (even whites) with out Cleric staying at 80-100% mana all the time.  In fact if we have to stop its becasue I need more mana to pull with.  And what I know of Clerics is from watching this guy keep us alive.  He melees at lvl 45, and asks to let the low blue stuff agro him to keep his Defense skills maxed.  Maybe you are an awesome cleric (don't know you're anon here) but the guy I group with is also a great cleric.  He can do damage and heal.  there is more to the Cleric than medding.<br><br>Neptunis<br>lvl 45 DE SK<br>Vesheen Server <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
